Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula has outlined additional measures to further curb the spread of the coronavirus. Mbalula says this won't be an easy discussion, but parties are committed to concluding it. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says there are plans to regulate the taxi industry. According to Mbalula, this won't be an easy discussion, but parties are committed to concluding it. READ: Mbalula: Government trying to resolve taxi industry dispute "We do have plans focused on fully regulating the taxi industry and the formalisation of the taxi industry," he said. Mbalula also says over the last few weeks the government has been in productive discussions with the banking association on further relief measures for the taxi industry. The minister was giving an update on amended regulations and further plans to combat the spread of COVID-19. The Economic Cluster ministers will unpack plans for South Africa.